Pub. L. No. 103&hyph;66, Title VI, Section 6001(a)(3), 107 Stat. 312 (approved August 10, 1993) (Reconciliation
Act).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
2. In compliance with the provision of the Reconciliation Act, the Department of Commerce released a report on February
10, 1994, which made a preliminary identification of 200 megahertz of spectrum for reallocation from Federal Government
to private sector use, including 50 megahertz at 2390&hyph;2400 MHz, 2402&hyph;2417 MHz, and 4660&hyph;4685 MHz
